reactions.description: Introduces the second biaryl-ether crosslink between bht2 and hpg4 in the vancomycin and balhimycin precursor. The reaction occures while the vancomycin precursor is bound to the PCP of module 6 or 7. The enzyme only accepts the chlorinated precursor.
Introduces the second biaryl-ether crosslink between bht2 and hpg4 in the vancomycin and balhimycin precursor

The reaction might be less specific than depicted in the reaction SMARTS. There is no detailed study on the specificity so far. The reaction occurs probably while the precursor peptide backbone is bound to the NRPS as shown for the closely related vancomycin biosynthesis (doi:10.1002/ANIE.200461278).
